<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12145c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12145c">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12145c"> 145(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> SP sends Benignus into / fire</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&laquo;On construisit une cabane; la moiti&eacute; fut faite de branches vertes; l&apos;autre moiti&eacute; de branchages secs. Le mage entra dans la partie de bois encore ver, et l&apos;un des serviteurs se P, nomm&eacute; Bineus (Benignus), fut enferm&eacute; dans l&apos;autre partie faite de bois sec. La cabane ayant &eacute;t&eacute; ferm&eacute;e, on y mit le feu en pr&eacute;sence de toute la foule. Et il arriva, &agrave; la pri&egrave;re de P, que la partie o&ugrave; se trouvait le mage fut consum&eacute;e par les flammes; seul, le v&ecirc;tement du saint demeura intact. &laquo;Bineus, comme il est dit des trois jeunes hommes, ne fut point atteint par les flammes, ni la partie de la cabane o&ugrave; il se trouvait, mais le v&ecirc;tement du mage fut consum&eacute; par le feu. <br><font color="green">[70: &ldquo;&hellip; the hut was then made, one half being of green branches and the other half of dry faggots. The Druid then entered the house of green wood, and the youth Benignus was shut up in the dry part, the door was closed and fastened, and fire applied to it in the presence of the crowd; and it happened through Patrick&apos;s prayers that the part where the Druid was, was entirely consumed, whilst none of the Saint&apos;s tunic was burnt. Benignus, like the three young men in the fiery furnace, was untouched by the flames, as was that part of the house he was in, but the magician&apos;s tunic was entirely destroyed.]</font> <small> Riguet, Abb&eacute; <a name="RTSP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RTSP"><cite title="source">Saint Patrice</cite></a> (1911) 84</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
